Visitors to Lesotho must travel through, or transit via, South Africa.
Since 18 March, South Africa has put in place travel restrictions and visa requirements for individuals from countries affected by coronavirus, including the United Kingdom. This impacts British Nationals wishing to enter and leave Lesotho. On 23 March the South African President announced further restrictions for everyone in South Africa. British Nationals in Lesotho are not currently permitted to leave Lesotho by road into South Africa without a visa.
British Nationals are currently permitted to transit through OR Tambo International Airport in Johannesburg if they are continuing to another international destination and their route does not involved passing through South African immigration controls.
Follow our travel advice for South Africa and consult your nearest South African High Commission for further information.
See advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
